<paragraph blockId="18.[140,1108,1257,1425]" pageId="18" pageNumber="375">
This Holarctic species was recorded from 
<collectingRegion box="[663,845,1293,1319]" country="Canada" name="New Brunswick" pageId="18" pageNumber="375">New Brunswick</collectingRegion>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Baranowski" box="[890,1107,1293,1319]" firstAuthor="Baranowski" pageId="18" pageNumber="375" pagination="1 - 149" refId="ref22548" refString="Baranowski R (1993) Revision of the genus Leiodes Latreille of North and Central America (Coleoptera: Leiodidae). Entomological Scandinavia Supplement 42: 1 - 149." type="journal article" year="1993">Baranowski (1993)</bibRefCitation>
based on the above record (
<figureCitation box="[463,533,1328,1355]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="16.[140,174,1622,1644]" captionTargetBox="[140,1109,827,1603]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[141,1109,828,1602]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Fig. 5. Distribution of Colenis impunctata, Liocyrtusa luggeri, Leiodes contaminabilis, Leiodes impersonata, Leiodes neglecta, Leiodes puncticollis, Leiodes rufipes, and Leiodes triepkei in Atlantic Canada." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3770892" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3770892/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="375">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). It apparently prefers rather sandy habitats, e.g., sandy meadows with low vegetation, clearing, forest plantations, or other open country, and is rarely found in forests (
<bibRefCitation author="Baranowski" box="[520,723,1398,1425]" firstAuthor="Baranowski" pageId="18" pageNumber="375" pagination="1 - 149" refId="ref22548" refString="Baranowski R (1993) Revision of the genus Leiodes Latreille of North and Central America (Coleoptera: Leiodidae). Entomological Scandinavia Supplement 42: 1 - 149." type="journal article" year="1993">Baranowski 1993</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
